reviews.review_text: Charlie don't surf OR DOES HE? ...and one of the greatest Cumberland Blues of all time.

This Is One terrifically and finely exemplary performance from 1981. Jerry is balls-to-the-walls, peddle-to-the-metal all-way throughout. Everyone else follows suit.

Unbelievers: check out the Estimated. Pause and consider...Selah!

This is an: Awe...oh...sssummmm.... seventeen out of five stars.

Certified.

U.S.D.A. Prime

da comptone Some early flubbs, feedback problems and patch pitch mismatches on the recording side give way to one of the most sparklingly great shows and clear recordings  you can hear. Keep in mind that the EQ should be adjusted a dB or 2 down in the middle with a straight slant up to 4 or 5 dB up on either end, as this SBD is quite flat and a bit too middle-rich.
